text:
Farrah Lynn Abraham (born May 31, 1991) is an American reality television personality and pornography actress. She was born in Omaha, Nebraska, and raised in Council Bluffs, Iowa and Austin, Texas.
Abraham is known for starring in "16 and Pregnant" in 2009, which documented the pregnancies and first months of motherhood for several young women. Later that year she was cast in the spin-off series "Teen Mom", and appeared in each of its four seasons until its conclusion in 2012.
In 2012, she wrote her first memoir "My Teenage Dream Ended". The book made it onto "The New York Times" Best Seller List.
Abraham began starring in sex tapes and pornography videos since 2014.
